        </symbolPack>
    </GeneDef>
    
    <GeneDef>
        <defName>EBSA_AcidSpew</defName>
        <label>acid spew</label>
        <description>Carriers grow glands in the neck that generate and store a sticky acid substance, along with acid-tolerant tissues in the mouth. They can spew this acid over an area, where it will stick to enemies and burn them.</description>
        <iconPath>UI/Icons/Genes/Gene_AcidSpray</iconPath>
        <displayCategory>Ability</displayCategory>
        <marketValueFactor>1.5</marketValueFactor>
        <abilities>
            <li>EBSA_AcidSpew</li>
        </abilities>
        <descriptionHyperlinks>
            <AbilityDef>EBSA_AcidSpew</AbilityDef>
        </descriptionHyperlinks>
        <biostatMet>-2</biostatMet>
        <symbolPack>
            <prefixSymbols>
                <li><symbol>acid</symbol></li>
                <li><symbol>acer</symbol></li>
                <li><symbol>acri</symbol></li>
                <li><symbol>oxo</symbol></li>
            </prefixSymbols>
            <suffixSymbols>
                <li><symbol>spewer</symbol></li>
                <li><symbol>spitter</symbol></li>
            </suffixSymbols>
        </symbolPack>
    </GeneDef>
    
    <GeneDef>
        <defName>EBSA_BloodSpew</defName>
        <label>blood spew</label>
        <description>Users have an organ in their neck that can pierce the wall of their neck and project blood into an area at a high enough velocity to even pierce through steel. Even if the pawn does not fall unconcious due to the bloodloss, the organ will be unusable for a time as it repairs the vein and throat wall.\n\nHemogenic pawns develop this organ slightly differently, and will use hemogen for this spray instead of blood, which also allows them to use it more often.</description>
        <iconPath>UI/Icons/Genes/Gene_AcidSpray</iconPath>
        <geneClass>EBSGFramework.SpawnAgeLimiter</geneClass><!--Earliest tier that processes abilities-->
        <displayCategory>Ability</displayCategory>
        <marketValueFactor>1.5</marketValueFactor>
        <customEffectDescriptions>
            <li>Gives Blood spew ability</li>
            <li>If pawn is hemogenic, blood spew has lower cooldown and uses hemogen instead of blood</li>
        </customEffectDescriptions>
        <displayOrderInCategory>90</displayOrderInCategory>
        <biostatMet>-2</biostatMet>
        <symbolPack>
            <prefixSymbols>
                <li><symbol>hemo</symbol></li>
            </prefixSymbols>
            <suffixSymbols>
                <li><symbol>spewer</symbol></li>
            </suffixSymbols>
        </symbolPack>
        <modExtensions>
            <li Class="EBSGFramework.EBSGExtension">
                <geneAbilities>
                    <li>
                        <forbiddenGenes>
                            <li>Hemogenic</li>
                        </forbiddenGenes>
                        <abilities>
                            <li>EBSA_BloodSpew</li>
                        </abilities>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <requireOneOfGenes>
                            <li>Hemogenic</li>
                        </requireOneOfGenes>
                        <abilities>
                            <li>EBSA_BloodSpew_Hemogen</li>
                        </abilities>
                    </li>
                </geneAbilities>
            </li>
        </modExtensions>
    </GeneDef>

    <GeneDef>
        <defName>EBSA_Chemburst</defName>
        <label>chemburst</label>
